Enum Class SaveDataType

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<SaveDataType>
com.comp2042.enums.SaveDataType
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<SaveDataType>, Constable
public enum SaveDataType extends Enum<SaveDataType>
Represents the different types of data that can be saved and loaded in the game.

Each enum corresponds to a specific line number defined in SaveData.

  • HIGHSCORE : The highest score for no timer.
  • HIGHSCORE_5 : High score for the timer of 5-minute mode.
  • HIGHSCORE_10 : High score for the timer of 10-minute.
  • HIGHSCORE_15 : High score for the timer of 15-minute mode.
  • HIGHSCORE_20 : High score for the timer of 20-minute mode.
  • LEFT : Keyboard shortcut for moving left.
  • RIGHT : Keyboard shortcut for moving right.
  • DOWN : Keyboard shortcut for moving down.
  • ROTATE : Keyboard shortcut for rotating pieces.
  • HOLD : Keyboard shortcut for holding a piece.
  • PAUSE : Keyboard shortcut for pausing the game.
  • RESTART : Keyboard shortcut for restarting the game.
  • HARDDROP : Keyboard shortcut for hard dropping a piece.
  • MUSIC : Volume setting for the background music.
  • BUTTONS : Paths and volume setting for button sounds.
  • CLEARLINES : Volume setting for line clear sound.
  • TOGGLE_HOLD : Boolean setting to show/hide hold piece.
  • TOGGLE_NEXT : Boolean setting to show/hide next piece preview.
  • TOGGLE_GHOST : Boolean setting to show/hide ghost piece.
  • TOGGLE_CONTROLS : Boolean setting to show/hide keyboard controls.
